            <p>
              Since designing the second style guide for the homepage, I worked closely with our engineering team to dig into the existing grid on the homepage and see how to incorporate more flexibility in designs with this new layout of the sign in badge and fullbleed banner.
              <br>
              <br>
              The grid is made up of a sixteen column system where individual columns bind together to act as a few large columns. After talking with the engineers, I was able to work out new designs for this space that accomodate a focal point in imagery, as currently the fullbleed image acts only as a background.
              <br>
              <br>
              I created a rudimentary style guide and shared it with a partner design team; they were able to work with it to create new banners that both fit within our guidelines of human and personal, while also promoting their new product in a fun and interesting way.
              <br>
              <br>
              Additionally, I modified the sign in badge to better fit within the grid structure at both desktop and tablet, and I’ve proposed future tablet A/B tests to see how the sign in badge can be shifted at tablet sizing.
            </p>
